The death toll of initiates in the Eastern Cape has now risen to 15 following the deaths of three more initiates this week.  One of the deceased had signs of having been assaulted, according to provincial health spokesman Sizwe Kupelo. While families of more than 15 000 young men including sons of AmaMpondo senior royal Prince Mlamli Ndamase, South African Airways CEO Vuyani Jarana, veteran government official Masiza Mazizi and Cofimvaba businesswoman Colina Sakawuli are happily hosting iimigidi, 15 other families are mourning and organising burials of their sons. Of the initiation deaths‚ nine are in the OR Tambo district of which five died in Mthatha alone‚ and two at KuKhambi village. Five initiates died in Mthatha alone, two at KuKhambi village.  ​Cooperative  governance and traditional Affairs MEC Fikile Xasa this afternoon closed down a Mthatha illegal traditional initiation school and rescued 19 initiates.   Initiation death toll in the province’s now stands at 17 following a third death reported in Amathole district, this afternoon. Some of the rescued initiates were reunited… December 21, 2017 The initiation death toll in the Eastern Cape has increased to 12 and with still some weeks to go before the season draws to a close, authorities are calling for parents to be more involved in their initiate sons’ welfare. The four most recent deaths have been reported from King… December 18, 2017 While thousands of families are ululating and dancing in celebration at the homecoming of their sons from initiation schools, at least 15 families are mourning the loss of theirs. Some died only days before they were to graduate from their initiation school and homecoming preparations were already in full swing,… December 21, 2017